[[File:Glacis Road, Gibraltar.jpg|thumb|Glacis Road]]
'''Glacis Road''' is a road in northern end of the [[British Overseas Territories|British Overseas Territory]] of [[Gibraltar]], the southwestern end of which is the junction with the Waterport Roundabout, where [[Waterport Road]] and [[Queensway, Gibraltar|Queensway]] also intersect. From the roundabout, Glacis Road extends to the northeast. At its mid portion, the road intersects with [[Bayside Road]], at which point it changes course to a southeast direction. Its eastern end intersects with [[Winston Churchill Avenue]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Resurfacing of Part of Glacis Road junction with Waterport Roundabout|url=http://vox.gi/local/4607-resurfacing-of-part-of-glacis-road-junction-with-waterport-roundabout.html|accessdate=2 May 2013|newspaper=Vox - The Truly Independent Gibraltar Newspaper|date=10 March 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Map of Glacis Road|url=https://maps.google.com/?q=36.147098,-5.352600&num=1&t=h&z=20|work=maps.google.com|publisher=Google Maps|accessdate=2 May 2013}}</ref> The North District office of the [[Royal Gibraltar Post Office]] is located on Glacis Road.<ref>{{cite web|title=Postal & Philatelic |url=http://www.gibraltar.gov.gi/postal-a-philatelic |work=gibraltar.gov.gi |publisher=Government of Gibraltar |accessdate=2 May 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130425051748/http://gibraltar.gov.gi/postal-a-philatelic |archivedate=25 April 2013 |df= }}</ref>

