{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians --> | name = Lama | image = Lama (Lviv).JPG | caption = Lama performing in [[Lviv]] | image_size = 300px | background = group_or_band | alias = | origin = [[Kiev|Kyiv]], {{UKR}} | genre = [[Pop rock]], [[alternative dance]], [[psychedelic pop]] | years_active = 2005- | label = | associated_acts = | website = {{URL|lama.com.ua}} | current_members = Natalia Dzeňkiv, Andriy, Zurik, Zi-Zi | past_members = }} '''Lama''' is a pop/rock band based in [[Ukraine]]. It became popular after release of their first singles: "Meni tak treba" (I Need So) and "Moje sertse" (My Heart). Their third single was "Litak" (Airplane). Lama's first album ''Meni tak treba'' was released in autumn 2006. The active members of Lama are [[Natalia Dzenkiv]] (vocals, lyrics), Andriy (guitar), Zurik (bass guitar) and Zi-Zi (drums). In 2007 Lama got the [[MTV Europe Music Awards 2007|Best Ukrainian act]] award of [[MTV Europe Music Awards]].
