'''''The Blooms of Banjeli''''' is a Togolese short documentary film directed by [[Carlyn Saltman]]. The 29-minute film includes footage from 1914 but not released until 1986 or 1987.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.therai.org.uk/film/volume-ii-contents/the-blooms-of-banjeli-technology-and-gender-in-west-african-ironmaking/|title=The Blooms of Banjeli: Technology and Gender in West African Ironmaking|publisher=Therai.org.uk|accessdate=28 December 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303174530/http://www.therai.org.uk/film/volume-ii-contents/the-blooms-of-banjeli-technology-and-gender-in-west-african-ironmaking/|archivedate=3 March 2016|df=}}</ref> It documents [[Banjeli]], from iron-smelting technology to local rituals and sexual prohibitions.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.der.org/films/blooms-of-banjeli.html|title=The Blooms Of Banjeli: Technology and Gender in African Ironmaking|publisher=Der.org|accessdate=28 December 2012}}</ref>

